---
import Layout from '../layouts/Layout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';
---

<Layout title="About — Museum of Giving" description="The story behind the Museum of Giving.">
  <main class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6">
    <!-- Back link -->
    <nav class="pt-8 pb-4">
      <a
        href="/"
        class="text-museum-muted text-sm hover:text-museum-text transition-colors inline-flex items-center gap-1"
      >
        <span>&larr;</span> Museum
      </a>
    </nav>

    <article class="pb-16 pt-4">
      <h1 class="font-display text-4xl sm:text-5xl font-bold tracking-tight mb-10">
        About the Museum
      </h1>

      <div class="space-y-6 text-museum-muted leading-relaxed">
        <p>
          In 1998, someone donated to Amnesty International online. The receipt that came back looked almost identical to an e-commerce order confirmation. Item: one human rights donation. Qty: 1. It was unremarkable and, for that exact reason, remarkable.
        </p>

        <p>
          That moment captured something we keep forgetting: the way nonprofits ask for money is a mirror of how the world communicates. From hand-painted war bond posters to AI-optimized donation forms, every era's technology reshapes the act of giving.
        </p>

        <p>
          The Museum of Giving exists to document this evolution. Not the history of philanthropy itself — there are books for that — but the <em>artifacts</em>. The actual posters, letters, web pages, text messages, and social posts through which organizations have asked ordinary people to help.
        </p>

        <p>
          We believe these artifacts deserve to be preserved. Many are already gone. Early donation pages from the 1990s have vanished from the internet. Direct mail letters from the 1960s sit in basements, fading. Telethon footage is locked in broadcast archives. Each one tells a story about how we learned to give.
        </p>
      </div>

      <hr class="border-museum-border my-12" />

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">
          Brought to you by Dataro
        </h2>
        <div class="space-y-4 text-museum-muted leading-relaxed">
          <p>
            <a
              href="https://dataro.com"
              target="_blank"
              rel="noopener noreferrer"
              class="underline underline-offset-2 hover:text-museum-text transition-colors"
            >
              Dataro
            </a>
            builds AI for nonprofits. We work with hundreds of the world's leading nonprofit organizations, helping them use data and machine learning to raise more for their missions.
          </p>
          <p>
            We built this museum because we spend every day thinking about how nonprofits fundraise — and we realized nobody was preserving the history of how they got here.
          </p>
        </div>
      </section>

      <hr class="border-museum-border my-12" />

      <section>
        <h2 class="font-display text-2xl font-semibold mb-6">
          Contribute
        </h2>
        <p class="text-museum-muted leading-relaxed mb-6">
          The museum grows through community contributions. If you have access to old fundraising materials — donation forms, appeal letters, campaign screenshots, anything — we want to hear from you.
        </p>
        <a
          href="/submit"
          class="inline-block px-6 py-3 bg-museum-text text-white text-sm font-medium tracking-wide rounded-sm hover:bg-museum-muted transition-colors"
        >
          Submit an Artifact
        </a>
      </section>
    </article>
  </main>

  <Footer />
</Layout>
